# Round Summary: Claude + Codex + Gemini

## Position Summaries

**Claude:**
Agrees defects are real but reframes cause: not "sync failure" but **unfinished design decisions**. Prioritizes: (1) reflect tick-daemon's Stage 1 async decision back into world-ontology as SOT, (2) resolve death-reincarnation §4 procedure model choice (blocks succession-tax-economy chain), (3) fix constitution article count (27 vs claimed 28+). Constants can wait.

**Codex:**
Conceptual charters pass directionally. Implementation-level still fails: constant contracts and 10ms SLA unspecified. Governance criteria are stricter than design coherence.

**Gemini:**
